Gluten is a protein found in certain foods. There is no gluten in beef and beef jerky doesn’t naturally contain any gluten. But it can become present in jerky in the form of marinades, the base sauce used to flavour the meat. Common jerky ingredients like soy sauce, sweet soy sauce, and BBQ sauce contain gluten. Some of Beef Chief jerky contains gluten. Some don’t. If you are gluten intolerant please check the warnings on each flavour before consuming.

